headlines.description: — The Philadelphia 76ers weren't playing well, and worse than that, Joel Embiid thought he was playing soft.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Harden help 76ers blow by Knicks to win 8th straight

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic and the Dallas Mavericks had trailed from the opening bucket when the crowd erupted at the sight of retired star Dirk Nowitzki on the video boards late in the first half.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs top Lakers 124-115 to celebrate Nowitzki statue

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown knocked down his shots in the fourth quarter. And then he knocked down Bucks star Giannis Antetokounmpo.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum has 41, Celtics push back on Giannis, Bucks 139-118

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole is far from a finished product, and the fourth-year guard showed both signs of brilliance and struggles controlling his emotions on the big Christmas Day basketball stage.
headlines.shortLinkText: With Curry out, Poole scores 32 and Warriors beat Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had another monster triple-double, Aaron Gordon threw down a pivotal dunk that stood up after a review in overtime and the Denver Nuggets rallied for a 128-125 victory over the Phoenix Suns on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Nuggets outlast Suns 128-125 in OT; Booker sidelined
